"title": "5399: luxury",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5399",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Opulence or grandeur of lifestyle which may be associated with wealth or status, especially royalty. Scripture warns of the dangers of unnecessary displays of luxury but encourages the right kind of splendour to reflect the glory and honour due to God.</p>\n<h2>Examples of luxurious lifestyles</h2>\n<h3>The opulence of Solomon's court</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs10:21\">1KI 10:21</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr9:20\">2CH 9:20</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs4:22-1Kgs4:24\">1KI 4:22–4:24</a> <em>Solomon's daily provisions</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs7:1\">1KI 7:1</a> <em>Solomon's palace</em><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs10:18-1Kgs10:20\">1KI 10:18–10:20</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr9:17-2Chr9:19\">2CH 9:17–9:19</a></p>\n<h3>Luxury enjoyed by other kings</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:25\">LUK 7:25</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:8\">MAT 11:8</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam8:11-1Sam8:17\">1SA 8:11–8:17</a> <em>Samuel warns Israel about what a king will demand of them</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:2\">2SA 7:2</a> <em>David</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr32:27-2Chr32:29\">2CH 32:27–32:29</a> <em>Hezekiah</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth1:4-Esth1:7\">EST 1:4–1:7</a> <em>Xerxes</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:30\">DAN 4:30</a> <em>Nebuchadnezzar</em></p>\n<h3>Luxury enjoyed by the wealthy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:19\">LUK 16:19</a></strong> <em>The rich man in Jesus Christ's parable.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa3:18-Isa3:23\">ISA 3:18–3:23</a> <em>upper-class women of Zion</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos6:4-Amos6:6\">AMO 6:4–6:6</a> <em>the wealthy of Israel</em></p>\n<h3>Luxury accompanying high status</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:41-Gen41:43\">GEN 41:41–41:43</a></strong> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth6:7-Esth6:8\">EST 6:7–6:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth8:15\">EST 8:15</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:29\">DAN 5:29</a> <em>Daniel</em></p>\n<h3>Luxury enjoyed by a bride</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps45:13-Ps45:15\">PSA 45:13–45:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:10\">ISA 61:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:32\">JER 2:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:2\">REV 21:2</a></p>\n<h2>Luxury and poverty</h2>\n<h3>Luxury at the expense of the poor</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:4-Jas5:5\">JAS 5:4–5:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer22:13-Jer22:14\">JER 22:13–22:14</a> <em>King Jehoiakim</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:3\">EZK 34:3</a> <em>the leaders of Israel</em></p>\n<h3>Luxury brings responsibility to the poor</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:18\">1TI 6:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer22:15-Jer22:16\">JER 22:15–22:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:20-Luke16:21\">LUK 16:20–16:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:8\">LUK 19:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:34-Acts4:35\">ACT 4:34–4:35</a></p>\n<h2>The perils of luxury</h2>\n<h3>Luxury brings a false sense of security</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:19\">LUK 12:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job31:24-Job31:25\">JOB 31:24–31:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:28\">PRO 11:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:17\">1TI 6:17</a></p>\n<h3>Luxury distracts from God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:15\">DEU 32:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut8:13-Deut8:14\">DEU 8:13–8:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:22\">MAT 13:22</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:19\">MRK 4:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:14\">LUK 8:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:21-Matt19:24\">MAT 19:21–19:24</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:21-Mark10:23\">MRK 10:21–10:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:21-Luke18:24\">LUK 18:21–18:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:10\">1TI 6:10</a></p>\n<h3>Earthly luxury does not last</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:19\">MAT 6:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov23:5\">PRO 23:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov27:24\">PRO 27:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa13:22\">ISA 13:22</a> <em>The luxurious lifestyle of the wicked will be swept away by God's judgment</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:1-Jas5:3\">JAS 5:1–5:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:7-Rev18:9\">REV 18:7–18:9</a></p>\n<h2>The right attitude to luxury</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:11-Phil4:12\">PHP 4:11–4:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:7\">1SA 2:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job1:21\">JOB 1:21</a></p>\n<h2>The true source of beauty</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:3-1Pet3:4\">1PE 3:3–3:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:9-1Tim2:10\">1TI 2:9–2:10</a></p>\n<h2>Luxury reflecting God's glory</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:3-Exod25:9\">EXO 25:3–25:9</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:5-Exod35:9\">EXO 35:5–35:9</a> <em>materials for the tabernacle</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:4-Exod28:5\">EXO 28:4–28:5</a> <em>the priestly garments</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs6:14-1Kgs6:35\">1KI 6:14–6:35</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr3:4-2Chr3:14\">2CH 3:4–3:14</a> <em>the splendour of Solomon's temple</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:1\">MRK 13:1</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:5\">LUK 21:5</a> <em>the magnificence of Herod's temple</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:15-Rev21:21\">REV 21:15–21:21</a> <em>the glory of the new Jerusalem</em></p>",
